Arctic monkeys move gig in Glasgow because of illness Alex Turners
The rock band Arctic monkeys has postponed an appearance in Glasgow, after their lead singer of laryngeal inflammation is ill.
The band from Sheffield should play in the water on Friday.
Because of the illness of lead singer Alex Turner, the concert must now be transferred, however.
The announcement of the band came after it had already had to postpone an appearance at the LG Arena in Birmingham on Thursday.
In a statement on their official website shared the Arctic monkeys with: "After the decision to cancel the show at the LG Arena in Birmingham tonight, as well as on medical advice, the Arctic monkeys also need to cancel the show at the Hydro in Glasgow on Friday, November 1."
"A laryngeal inflammation was diagnosed with Alex Turner, so he cannot, unfortunately, occur."
The show at the LG Arena in Birmingham will now take place on November 20, the Hydro in Glasgow was laid on November 21.
All tickets remain valid for these shows.
We apologize for the inconvenience this has caused to all ticket holders.
If you need further assistance, please contact the customer service at the store where you bought your ticket.
